combating hiv aids in india public private partnerships are necessary for success siepr siepr stanford institute for economic policy research search the site enter your keywords main links home about siepr research at siepr education at siepr events at siepr people at siepr publications at siepr economics in the news support siepr contact us stay connected stay connected banner home publications profile display combating hiv aids in india public private partnerships are necessary for success type scid working paper 309 author s robert bollinger amita gupta published 12 1 06 region india download pdf abstract the authors argue that in order to optimize hiv aids care in india the essential requirement is to engage the private sector effectively alongside the public sector they argue as well for a combination of strategies that are designed for the conditions encountered at state and local levels these strategies importantly include regulations on the activities of pharmacies and providers of health services who are competent to ensure a minimum standard of care to hiv infected citizens regulatory strategies should be complemented by effective communication to and education of the public the authors stress the importance of training and quality assurance of physicians via such re certification processes as continuing medical education they also stress the importance of introducing standards for measurement of access to services their quality and clinical outcomes stanford university economics department stanford center for international development public policy program site map economic summit
